<br />
<br />I'm having some problems understanding the processor, I think. Please bear with my ignorance. My original thought was that using the microcontroller I could set the 2A03's address bus pins to the address I want to write (such as $4007), the data bus pins to the data I want to write (such as $F8), enable pin 34 for writing, and that data would go into that address at the next clock cycle or so. By having the microcontroller write different data to different addresses (it is actually reading in analog voltages and converting them to digital - this part is done) I could update frequency values, duty cycles, etc. Is it not possible to do that simply, putting the bulk of the work into the microcontroller's program? Do I have to instead write a program to the 2A03 and then have the microcontroller constantly update that program's code?</div>

