					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Have something which feeds data to the 2A03 as memory reads. All it needs to feed is $A2 xx $8C yy $40. This corresponds to LDY #xx, STY $40yy. Then your circuit could just keep asserting NMI every 6+7 clocks. It would need to feed some data for the NMI vector read, but that wouldn't need to be anything specific as long as the values didn't fall within I/O space. I bet a pretty minimal circuit could feed this fake instruction stream to the 2A03.</div>

