				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That "discrete ROM" approach is really simple. The '138 decodes the address into 8 individual enable lines, each of which "enable" that byte of the ROM. The two data values you provide are simple. The other values are gated by the remaining '245, and generated by a clever combination of gates (and choice of which opcodes to use).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

